7. AI-GENERATED OUTPUT AND AUTOMATED ACTIONS

The Software uses AI models operated by third parties to generate code,
documentation, tests, and other output, and enables AI agents to perform
automated actions on your behalf. You acknowledge and agree that:

  (a) AI-generated output is provided "as is" and may contain errors, bugs,
      security vulnerabilities, fabricated information, or material that
      resembles copyrighted or patented third-party work;
  (b) you are solely responsible for reviewing, testing, and validating all
      AI-generated output before deploying or distributing it;
  (c) AI agents may execute shell commands, create and modify files,
      interact with source control, and take other automated actions with
      the same permissions as your user account. You are responsible for
      the consequences of those actions and for maintaining backups;
  (d) a single work item may fan out across multiple agents and generate a
      large volume of API requests, and all resulting third-party API
      charges are your sole responsibility. You should configure spending
      caps and usage alerts directly with your AI provider.

